{"page_content": "Practices for Governing Agentic AI Systems\nYonadav Shavit\u2217\nSandhini Agarwal\u2217\nMiles Brundage\u2217\nSteven Adler\nCullen O\u2019Keefe\nRosie Campbell\nTeddy Lee\nPamela Mishkin\nTyna Eloundou\nAlan Hickey\nKatarina Slama\nLama Ahmad\nPaul McMillan\nAlex Beutel\nAlexandre Passos\nDavid G. Robinson\nAbstract\nAgentic AI systems\u2014AI systems that can pursue complex goals with limited direct supervision\u2014\nare likely to be broadly useful if we can integrate them responsibly into our society. While such\nsystems have substantial potential to help people more e\ufb03ciently and e\ufb00ectively achieve their\nown goals, they also create risks of harm. In this white paper, we suggest a de\ufb01nition of agentic\nAI systems and the parties in the agentic AI system life-cycle, and highlight the importance of\nagreeing on a set of baseline responsibilities and safety best practices for each of these parties.\nAs our primary contribution, we o\ufb00er an initial set of practices for keeping agents\u2019 operations\nsafe and accountable, which we hope can serve as building blocks in the development of agreed\nbaseline best practices. We enumerate the questions and uncertainties around operationalizing\neach of these practices that must be addressed before such practices can be codi\ufb01ed. We then\nhighlight categories of indirect impacts from the wide-scale adoption of agentic AI systems, which\nare likely to necessitate additional governance frameworks.\nTable of Contents\n1\nIntroduction\n2\n2\nDe\ufb01nitions\n4\n2.1\nAgenticness, Agentic AI Systems, and \u201cAgents\u201d . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . .\n4\n2.2\nThe Human Parties in the AI Agent Life-cycle\n. . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . .\n5\n3\nPotential Bene\ufb01ts of Agentic AI Systems\n6\n3.1\nAgenticness as a Helpful Property . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . .\n6\n3.2\nAgenticness as an Impact Multiplier\n. . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . . .\n7\n4\nPractices for Keeping Agentic AI Systems Safe and Accountable\n7\n4.1", "metadata": {"producer": "LuaTeX-1.16.0", "creator": "LaTeX with hyperref", "creationdate": "2023-12-18T15:56:58+00:00", "source": "D:\\Users\\wpoga\\Documents\\Ebooks\\Artificial Intelligence\\practices-for-governing-agentic-ai-systems.pdf", "file_path": "D:\\Users\\wpoga\\Documents\\Ebooks\\Artificial Intelligence\\practices-for-governing-agentic-ai-systems.pdf", "total_pages": 23, "format": "PDF 1.5", "title": "", "author": "", "subject": "", "keywords": "", "moddate": "2023-12-18T15:56:58+00:00", "trapped": "", "modDate": "D:20231218155658Z", "creationDate": "D:20231218155658Z", "page": 0}, "type": "Document"}
